Men's Health Week is a time to raise awareness of diseases and illnesses that affect American men, as well as emphasize the importance of early detection and preventive health practices. It encourages men to evaluate their mental and physical health and live a healthy lifestyle. Regular visits to healthcare providers are crucial for men, as they tend to visit less often than women, missing out on critical treatments. The article also highlights the significance of emotional and mental health, addressing stigmas that prevent individuals from seeking treatment and recovery support services. The fiscal year 2019 Budget request to Congress includes $10 billion in new funding to address the opioid abuse and overdose epidemic and mental health. The National Helpline is available to provide referrals to local treatment facilities, support groups, and community-based organizations. Men's Health Week celebrates the advancements in men's healthcare while emphasizing the importance of prioritizing both physical and mental health.